 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> maître de cavalerie Khataios fils d'Hagèsarkhos, gymnasiarques Khèriadas fils de Timônax, Mnastoklès fils d'Aristeidas,
            Kléarkhos fils de Kléarkhos, ainsi que ceux des seniors <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>os fils de Philoxénos, <supplied reason="lost">Untel</supplied>
            fils d'Hippis, <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> master of riding Chataios son of Hagesarchos, gymnasiarchs Cheriadas son of Timonax, Mnastokles son of Aristeidas,
            Klearchos son of Klearchos, as well as those for seniors <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>os son of Philoxenos, <supplied reason="lost">So-and-so</supplied>
            son of Hippis, <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> il maestro d'equitazione Chataios figlio di Hagesarchos, i ginnasiarchi Cheriadas figlio di Timonax, Mnastokles figlio di Aristeidas,
            Klearchos figlio di Klearchos, così come <supplied reason="subaudible">i ginnasiarchi</supplied> dei seniores <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>os figlio di Philoxenos, <supplied reason="lost">il tale</supplied>
            figlio di Hippis, <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>[---] مدرب ركوب الخيل أو قائد الخيالة  خاتايوس بن هاجيسارخوس ومشرفي الجمنازيوم خيرياداس بن تيموناكتس ومناستوكليس بن أريستيداس وكلارتشوس بن كليارخوس، بالاضافة إلى أولئك لتدريب كبار السن [---] وس بن فيلوكسينوس و [فلان] بن هيبيس، [---].</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>For a more complete example of a dedication by the ephebes followed by their list, see <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr015200</ref>.</p>
	     <p>For the syntactical display of those lists, see <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2000"/>, pp. <citedRange>241-246</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
	   <p>At line 9, Marengo's interesting restoration is ruled out through autopsy of the stone. We should thus suppose with Luni that in this instance two 
	       gymnasiarchs of the elders were on duty. The list of ephebes, with the title <foreign xml:lang="grc">τριακάτιοι</foreign>, would have begun just 
	       under the break. See also <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/></bibl>, who suggests without arguing that this list might be one of the oldest. Besides,
	   he points out that the first mentioned of the gymnasiarchs for seniors might be <supplied reason="lost">Philis</supplied>kos son of Philoxenos, homonym of 
	   a priest of an unknown deity and belonging to a well-known family.</p>
            </div></body>
